<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="when-conj">when <strong><em>conj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /wen/    美 /wen/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>当...时：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When I was a child, my family lived in Beijing.
我小的时候，全家人都住在北京。</p><footer>北师大② – 6</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When in Rome do as the Romans do. 
入乡随俗。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>一...就...；那时：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We were about to go for a picnic when it began to rain. 
我们正要去野餐，这时天突然下起雨来。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Jack was working in the lab when the power cut occurred. 
停电时，杰克正在实验室里工作。</p><footer>2016 北京</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He had just fallen asleep when the telephone rang.
他刚睡着电话就响了。</p></div>

<p>注: 此时主句的时态通常是过去完成时、过去进 行时或含有was / were about to 的一般过去时。  </p>
<h4 id="3-if">3.★ <strong>[引导条件状语从句，相当于if] 如果：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Turn off the switch when anything goes wrong with the machine. 
如果机器发生故障，就关上开关。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>既然；考虑到：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Why use metal when you can use plastic?
既然能用塑料，为什么要用金属呢？</p></div>

<h4 id="5-even-though-sth-is-true">5.<strong>虽然；可是 even though sth is true:</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She claimed to be 18, when I knew she was only 16.
她自称18岁，可是据我所知她才16岁。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>It was April 29, 2011 <strong><em>_</em></strong> Prince William and Kate Middleton walked into the palace hall of the wedding ceremony.   （2011 福建改）  </li>
<li>She had just finished her homework <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ her mother asked her to practise playing the piano yesterday.  （2009 福建改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. when  2. when  </p></div>